SUMMARY:Oswego - Off We Go 
DESCRIPTION:Portland City Trail Walking Group\n**DESCRIPTION**: Let’s meet for a simple up and back and log some miles from downtown Oswego to Lewis & Clark\, along the mostly quiet paved bicycle path amoung the lovely trees and meadow. Beginning of the walk is hilly. Mid-way pit stop at the Nature Center (Tryon Creek).\n\n***RSVP ETIQUETTE: Thank you in advance for changing your RSVP from "Going" to "Not Going" or drop a note in the chat if your plans change.***\n\n**DISTANCE**: Six miles.\n\n**MEET AT:** Dang's Thai Kitchen parking lot. 670 North State Street\, Lake Oswego.\n\n**PARKING:** In the lot near the restaurant\; there's also nearby street parking on B Avenue or 7th.\n\n**LAUNCH TIME**: 10:00 A.M.\n\n**FITNESS LEVEL**: Expect a moderate pace for this paved walk.\n\n**ATTIRE**: Bring your layers and adventurous spirit.\n\n**GUESTS**: Guests welcome!\n\n**REPAST OPTION (or not):** Group preference.
